      "content": "That's a good start for the students to get the gist of it. I'm a bit worried though, some of the more conservative legal scholars might argue that this interpretation is just \"judicial activism\" and that the concept is actually much more limited in scope. How should I address those critics in my lesson so they understand why the substantive due process approach is the more legitimate one for protecting rights?",
